    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written to `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/rustling-wiggling-sloth.md`:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### Files to Create (4 new) + 1 Edit\n\n**1. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core implementation (mirrors `user-agent.ts`)\n- `Geo` interface: 7 optional string fields (`city`, `country`, `countryCode`, `region`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `timezone`)\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map with 10 entries (US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — reads Vercel `x-vercel-ip-*` headers, falls back to Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` for `countryCode`, derives `country` name from the map\n- `geo({ headers }: { headers: Headers }): Geo` — convenience wrapper (same shape as `userAgent()`)\n- `isInRegion(geo: Geo, regions: string[]): boolean` — case-insensitive `countryCode` check\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2: string): number` — Haversine formula in km; strict-mode safe with `??` for null→undefined conversion\n\n**2. `packages/next/geo.js`** — Public CJS entry point (exact mirror of `server.js` pattern)\n\n**3. `packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — TypeScript re-exports (exact mirror of `server.d.ts`); `Geo` exported as `export type`\n\n**4. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — Tests using `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` (no Jest needed), covering all 4 exports including NY→London distance (~5570km ±50km) and Cloudflare fallback\n\n**Edit `packages/next/package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical: f < **g** < h)\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types          # TypeScript strict check\npnpm --filter=next build          # Compile src/ → dist/\nnode --test packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts\n```",
